# BioLLMComposition — Project Architecture

## Goal

Predict **protein–DNA residue-level contact maps** by composing frozen
protein LMs (ESM2/ESM-C) with frozen DNA LMs (DNABERT-2) through
learnable cross-attention layers and a bilinear contact head.

Output shape: `(B, 2, R, L)` — two DNA strands × protein residues × DNA nucleotides.

## Repository Layout

```
biollmcomposition/
  models/              # Model registry (ESM2, ESM-C, DNABERT-2)
    __init__.py         # Unified get_model_info / load_model / load_tokenizer
    esm2.py             # ESM2 variants (8M→15B), dims, layer counts
    esmc.py             # ESM-C variants (300M, 600M)
    dnabert2.py         # DNABERT-2 (117M), emb_dim=768
  frameworks/           # Composition strategies
    __init__.py          # get_framework() dispatcher
    attention.py         # Cross-attention: prot queries each DNA strand separately
    composition.py       # LM-interleaved: DNA injected into ESM2 layers via cross-attn
  utils/
    contact_map.py       # Losses, metrics, dataset, masks, splitting helpers

scripts/
  00_precompute_tokens_and_labels.py   # Raw data → tokenized .pt
  01_split_datasets.py                 # .pt → train/val/test split indices
  02_run_training.py                   # Unified config-driven training (BCE loss)
  frameworks/
    attention_contactmap.py            # Standalone attention trainer (BCE)
    composition_contactmap.py          # Standalone composition trainer (BCE)
    attention_contactmap_focal_loss.py # Attention + focal loss + LR schedule
    composition_contactmap_focal_loss.py # Composition + focal loss + LR schedule

configs/
  precompute/        # YAML for 00_precompute
  splitting/         # YAML for 01_split
  training/          # YAML for 02_run_training and standalone scripts
```

